    <title> Multiple_Myeloma_Management_plan</title>
    <link id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>



        <h3 class="General">MANAGEMENT PLAN</h3>
        <h4 class="General">OBO Urgency</h4>
        <ul>
          <li class="General">Urgent Admission:</li>
          <ol class="General">
            <li class="hematology oncology emergency">Myeloma complications: Spinal Cord Compression, Acute Hypercalcemia, Acute Renal Failure, Neutropenic Sepsis</li>
          </ol>
          <li class="General">Urgent Referral (2 weeks):</li>
          <ol class="General ">
            <li class="hematology oncology">Suspected Myeloma (e.g., raised paraprotein, lytic bone lesions, or CRAB features)</li>
          </ol>
          <li class="General">Routine Referral:</li>
          <ol class="General ">
            <li class="hematology">Follow-up of stable Monoclonal Gammopathy of Undetermined Significance (MGUS)</li>
          </ol>
          <li class="General">Handling In-House:</li>
          <ol class="General ">
            <li class="hematology oncology">Not applicable for new diagnosis; requires immediate specialist referral</li>
          </ol>
        </ul>
        <h4 class="General">Patient-Specific Plan</h4>
        <ol>
          <li class="General">Want someone to listen in? (Patient partnership)</li>
          <li class="emergency">family coming?</li>
          <ol class="General">
            <li class="General">we can call ..... for you</li>
          </ol>
          <li class="General cns">Assess Mental Capacity</li>
          <li class="General">Consider Safeguarding issues</li>
          <li class="General">Initial Investigations
            <ul class="General">
              <li class="General"><em>Consent (ensure informed, check understanding)</em></li>
              <li class="General cvs hematology">Blood work: </li>
              <ul class="hematology oncology">
                <li><b>Myeloma Screen:</b> Serum protein electrophoresis & immunofixation, Serum Free Light Chains (SFLC), FBC, U&E, LFTs, Bone profile (Calcium), LDH, Beta-2 microglobulin</li>
              </ul>
              <li class="General cvs">Imaging: </li>
              <ul class="General">
                <li class="nephro urology">Urine dip stick & Bence-Jones Protein analysis</li>
                <li class="hematology oncology">Whole-body MRI (or Skeletal Survey if unavailable)</li>
              </ul>
              <li class="General cvs">Further Investigations</li>
              <ul class="General">
                <li class="General cvs">Specialized tests: </li>
                <ul class="hematology oncology">
                  <li>Bone Marrow Aspirate & Biopsy (for diagnosis, cytogenetics)</li>
                </ul>
              </ul>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <ol class="General">
          <li class="General">EXPLAIN FINDINGS</li>
            <ul>
                <li class="hematology oncology">Explain diagnosis of Myeloma (cancer of plasma cells)</li>
                <li class="hematology oncology">Explain CRAB criteria if present (Hyper<b>C</b>alcemia, <b>R</b>enal impairment, <b>A</b>nemia, <b>B</b>one lesions)</li>
            </ul>
    
          <li class="h3">ICE : Ideas, Concerns, Expectations </li>
          <ol>
            <li>Ideas: "What have you been told so far about this?"</li>
            <li>Concerns:
              <ul>
                <li>Pain, loss of independence, fractures</li>
                <li>Side effects of chemotherapy</li>
                <li>Prognosis / Is it curable?</li>
                <li>Impact on family and work</li>
                <li>Cancer</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Expectations:
              <ul>
                <li>Cure vs. Control of disease</li>
                <li>Symptom management, maintaining quality of life</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ol>
    
          <li class="General"><strong>PROVISIONAL DIAGNOSIS:</strong>
          <ol class="General">
            <li class="General">ANATOMICAL: </li>
            <ul>
              <li class="hematology">Bone Marrow</li>
            </ul>
            <li class="General">ETIOLOGICAL:
              <ul class="hematology oncology">
                <li class="hematology oncology">Clonal proliferation of malignant plasma cells</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="General">PATHOLOGICAL:</li>
            <ul>
              <li class="hematology oncology">Marrow infiltration, production of monoclonal paraprotein, osteoclast activation</li>
            </ul>
            <li class="General">CLINICAL:</li>
            <ul>
              <li class="hematology oncology">Multiple Myeloma - [Specify ISS/R-ISS Stage if known]</li>
            </ul>
          </ol>
          </li>
          
          <li class="General">Treatment Plan
            <ul class="General">
               <li class="General">Shared Decision-Making
                    <ul>
                        <li>Haematologist-led discussion of treatment pathway</li>
                        <li>Discuss transplant eligibility (based on age and fitness)</li>
                        <li>Discuss risks vs benefits of treatment regimens</li>
                    </ul>
               </li>
                <li class="General">Supportive Care (Crucial alongside specific treatment): 
                <ul class="hematology oncology">
                  <li>Analgesia for bone pain (WHO ladder, often requires opiates)</li>
                  <li>Bisphosphonates (e.g., Zoledronic acid) for bone protection & hypercalcemia</li>
                  <li>Management of renal impairment (hydration, avoid nephrotoxins like NSAIDs)</li>
                  <li>Management of anemia (blood transfusion, consider EPO)</li>
                  <li class="infectious">Infection prophylaxis (vaccinations [no live vaccines], consider prophylactic antibiotics)</li>
                  <li class="cvs">VTE prophylaxis (essential with certain treatments like IMiDs)</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li class="General">Specific treatment: 
                <ul class="hematology oncology">
                    <li><b>Induction Therapy (Chemotherapy):</b> Based on transplant eligibility.</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Common regimens include combinations of Proteasome Inhibitors (e.g., Bortezomib), Immunomodulatory drugs (IMiDs, e.g., Lenalidomide), and Corticosteroids (e.g., Dexamethasone).</li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li class="General">Consent</li>
              <li class="General">Non-Medical: 
                <ul class="General">
                  <li class="General">Psychological support</li>
                  <li class="General">Nutritional support / Dietitian input</li>
                  <li class="General">Social Prescribing (referral to link workers, support groups)</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li class="surgery">Surgical
                <ul class="ortho-specific">
                  <li>Vertebroplasty/Kyphoplasty for vertebral compression fractures</li>
                  <li>Orthopaedic fixation for pathological fractures</li>
                </ul>
                <ul class="hematology oncology">
                  <li>Autologous Stem Cell Transplant (ASCT) for eligible patients after induction</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="General">Patient Education
            <ul class="General">
              <li class="General">Warning Signs/Red Flags (Return immediately if):
                <ul class="hematology oncology emergency">
                  <li class="cns emergency">New or worsening severe back pain, leg weakness, numbness, or bladder/bowel changes (<b>Spinal Cord Compression</b>)</li>
                  <li class="cns emergency">Drowsiness, confusion, severe thirst, or constipation (<b>Hypercalcemia</b>)</li>
                  <li class="infectious emergency">Fever, chills, or any sign of serious infection (<b>Neutropenic Sepsis</b>)</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <ul class="General">
                <li class="General">Emergency Contacts:
                  <ol class="General">
                    <li class="emergency">999 - emergency</li>
                    <li class="hematology oncology">Haematology Day Unit / Specialist Nurse contact number</li>
                    <li class="General">111 - non emergency</li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <li class="General cns endocrine cvs">DVLA (Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency) Notification</li>
              <li class="General">Educational materials provided: 
                <ul class="General">
                  <li class="General">Leaflets / Pamphlets</li>
                  <li class="General">QR code for online</li>
                  <li class="General">Personalised Care Plan (written summary of consultation)</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li class="General">Useful resources/links: 
                <ul class="General">
                  <li class="hematology oncology">Myeloma UK</li>
                  <li class="hematology oncology">Macmillan Cancer Support</li>
                  <li class="hematology oncology">Blood Cancer UK</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
    
            <li class="General">Follow Up
              <ul class="General">
                <li class="General">Type:
                  <ul class="General">
                    <li class="General">Haematology outpatient clinic</li>
                  </ul>
                </li> 
                <li class="General">Frequency: 
                  <ul class="General">
                    <li class="hematology oncology">Regularly, as determined by haematology team based on treatment phase</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="General">Monitoring
                  <ul class="hematology oncology">
                    <li>Response to treatment via Paraprotein levels, Serum Free Light Chains, FBC</li>
                    <li>Monitoring renal function and calcium levels</li>
                    <li>Symptom review and assessment of treatment side effects</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="General">Specialist referrals: 
                  <ul class="General">
                    <li class="hematology oncology">Haematology (central to all management)</li>
                    <li class="rehab">Pain Management Clinic / Palliative Care</li>
                    <li class="nephro">Renal team (if significant renal impairment)</li>
                    <li class="ortho-specific">Orthopaedics (for pathological fractures)</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="General">Allied health:
                  <ul class="General">
                    <li class="rehab">Occupational Therapist</li>
                    <li class="rehab">Physiotherapist (for mobility and strength)</li>
                    <li class="rehab">Dietitian</li>
                    <li class="psychiatric">Clinical Psychologist / Counsellor</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            
          </li>
          <li class="General">Consider mandatory reporting duties (e.g., notifiable diseases)</li>
          <li class="General">Teach back
            <ul>
              <li>Patient tell the plan</li>
              <li> can you tell me what you understand about your condition?</li>
              <li> treatment?</li>
              <li> follow-up?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
    
          <li class="General">Summary of the plan</li>
          <ul>
            <li>doctor repeats the plan</li>
          </ul>
    
          <li class="General">Document the plan</li>
            <ul>
                <li class="ortho-specific">Offer Med 3 fit note if symptoms likely > 7 days</li>
                <li class="General">Clear, accurate, and contemporaneous documentation</li>
            </ul>
        </ol>
 



